This paper discusses exploration methods in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on comparing exploration in parameter space and action space, which falls under the category of optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses theoretical analyses and empirical comparisons, which could fall under the categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
